I would make this point differently and point out the following alternative view;

A large part of what allowed Japan to resist normalization of policy for so long was that China was exporting deflation and therefore allowing Japan to remain in their low rate paradigm well past the worst of the 2022 inflationary episode.

China easing while the global economy stays strong would likely necessitate a continued policy response of tightening that will narrow interest rate differentials & strengthen the yen, in my opinion.

